-Byrne</b><i> [holding answer 3 July 2006]:</i>
-It is the responsibility of the operators to ensure
-that each student employed on the seasonal agricultural workers scheme
-(SAWS) has a contract of employment and that it meets the terms and
-conditions of both the scheme and all appropriate employment
-legislation. Monitoring activities have found that many students
-employed on the SAWS are being paid as daily casual workers; a practice
